<dl id="n25156i"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n25" href="#n25156i">N25 (VI.B.15)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/n25all.htm#n25156i"> 156(i)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> Pantli nochtli / flag pear</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources"><font color="green">[Account of the attempts of Spanish missionaries after the <i>Conquest</i> to have prayers transliterated using Aztec ideograms]</font> <i>Pater noster</i> was written by a <mark>flag</mark> (<i><mark>pantli</mark></i>) and a prickly <mark>pear</mark> (<i><mark>nochtli</mark></i>), <small> Edward Clodd, <a name="ECSA1" href="../../ff/fdra/fdex.htm#ECSA1"><cite title="source">The Story of the Alphabet</cite></a>, rev. ed. (1913) 80</small></blockquote> <mm class="note">Raphael transcription: <a name="c14103g" href="c14all.htm#c14103g">VI.C.14:103(g)</a> </mm></dd> </dd></dl>
